How to remove the Statement / Theme Banners from YouTube After years of these super annoying YouTube banners, I hacked together a little script that removes them from the DOM upon finding one.
To run this, you need to install something like Tampermonkey (available for Firefox and Chrome) and create a new userscript with the following code:
// ==UserScript== // @name Fuck YouTube Theme banners // @namespace https://codef0x.dev // @version 1.
